55
00:02:40.027 --> 00:02:41.871
OH. NO. WAIT! LOOKIT!

56
00:02:41.895 --> 00:02:43.195
WHOA!

57
00:02:43.264 --> 00:02:44.264
OH. MY GOD.

58
00:02:44.298 --> 00:02:45.375
THIS IS A POLICE BADGE.

59
00:02:45.399 --> 00:02:46.565
OH. THAT'S SO COOL.

60
00:02:46.634 --> 00:02:48.545
WHY WOULD A COP
COME IN HERE. THOUGH?

61
00:02:48.569 --> 00:02:50.889
THEY DON'T SERVE DOUGHNUTS.

62
00:02:51.672 --> 00:02:52.815
YOU KNOW WHAT. ACTUALLY?

63
00:02:52.839 --> 00:02:54.451
COULD YOU DISCOVER
THE BADGE AGAIN?

64
00:02:54.475 --> 00:02:55.852
I THINK I CAN COME UP WITH
SOMETHING BETTER THAN THAT.

65
00:02:55.876 --> 00:02:57.543
PHOEBE

66
00:02:57.611 --> 00:02:59.289
I BET SOMEBODY'S
MISSING THAT BADGE.

67
00:02:59.313 --> 00:03:00.890
YEAH. I SHOULD
PROBABLY TAKE IT BACK.

68
00:03:00.914 --> 00:03:01.991
OOH. BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

69
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.348
WHILE I'M AT THE POLICE STATION

70
00:03:03.417 --> 00:03:05.195
I COULD CHECK THEIR
TEN MOST WANTED LIST.

71
00:03:05.219 --> 00:03:07.686
'CAUSE MY FRIEND FRITZY'S
BEEN NUMBER 11 FOR. LIKE. EVER

72
00:03:07.754 --> 00:03:08.953
SO THIS COULD BE HER YEAR.

73
00:03:10.491 --> 00:03:12.090
HEY. YOU GUYS.

74
00:03:12.159 --> 00:03:13.203
HEY. JOEY.

75
00:03:13.227 --> 00:03:14.159
HEY.

76
00:03:14.228 --> 00:03:16.161
HI.

77
00:03:16.230 --> 00:03:18.630
IS THAT. UH... IS THAT
MY SWEATSHIRT?

78
00:03:18.699 --> 00:03:19.631
OH. YES. IT IS.

79
00:03:19.700 --> 00:03:20.799
I'M SORRY. I BORROWED IT.

80
00:03:20.867 --> 00:03:22.234
I WAS COLD. I-I HOPE IT'S OKAY.

81
00:03:22.303 --> 00:03:24.236
UH. WELL. IT'S JUST THAT. UH...

82
00:03:24.305 --> 00:03:27.138
YOU KNOW. IF YOU'RE GOING TO BE
WEARING SOMEONE'S SWEATSHIRT

83
00:03:27.208 --> 00:03:28.685
SHOULDN'T IT BE
YOUR BOYFRIEND'S?

84
00:03:28.709 --> 00:03:30.141
AND I'M NOT HIM.

85
00:03:30.211 --> 00:03:32.811
I'M SORRY. I'LL GIVE
IT BACK TO YOU.

86
00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:33.812
NO. NO.

87
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:35.514
NO. IT'S GOING TO BE

88
00:03:35.583 --> 00:03:37.182
ALL SMELLING LIKE MONICA.

89
00:03:37.251 --> 00:03:39.251
ARE YOU SAYING I SMELL BAD?

90
00:03:39.320 --> 00:03:42.887
NO. NO. YOU SMELL LIKE A MEADOW.

91
00:03:44.258 --> 00:03:46.225
I'M SORRY. I...

92
00:03:49.396 --> 00:03:50.429
WHAT'S WITH HIM?

93
00:03:50.497 --> 00:03:51.697
OH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

94
00:03:51.765 --> 00:03:53.832
THE LAST TIME THAT
JOEY WENT TO A MEADOW

95
00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:56.535
HIS MOTHER WAS SHOT BY A HUNTER.

96
00:03:56.604 --> 00:03:58.403
HEY.

97
00:03:58.472 --> 00:03:59.816
HEY. LOOKIT! LOOK WHAT I FOUND.

98
00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:01.340
IT'S A POLICE BADGE.

99
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:02.941
WHAT'S THAT DOING HERE?

100
00:04:03.009 --> 00:04:04.843
I DON'T SEE ANY DOUGHNUTS.

101
00:04:06.813 --> 00:04:09.648
COPS AND DOUGHNUTS? COME ON.

102
00:04:09.717 --> 00:04:11.015
OH. OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

103
00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:12.729
IF CHANDLER HAD SAID IT.
YOU'D ALL BE ON THE FLOOR.

104
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:14.753
COPS? DOUGHNUTS? ME?

105
00:04:29.370 --> 00:04:30.902
OH!

106
00:04:32.873 --> 00:04:35.206
YEAH. I STILL DON'T KNOW.

107
00:04:35.276 --> 00:04:38.109
I'M SORRY. I JUST WANT TO MAKE
SURE I BOUGHT THE RIGHT COUCH.

108
00:04:38.178 --> 00:04:39.311
I NEED A COUCH THAT SAYS

109
00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:41.513
"KIDS WELCOME HERE"

110
00:04:41.582 --> 00:04:43.982
BUT THAT ALSO SAYS...

111
00:04:44.050 --> 00:04:46.685
"COME HERE TO ME."

112
00:04:48.322 --> 00:04:49.621
WHAT?

113
00:04:49.690 --> 00:04:52.023
YOU SAY THAT TO KIDS?

114
00:04:52.092 --> 00:04:53.358
NO. NO. NO.

115
00:04:53.427 --> 00:04:55.527
THE "COME HERE TO ME" IS...

116
00:04:55.596 --> 00:04:57.429
YOU KNOW. FOR THE LADIES.

117
00:04:58.999 --> 00:05:00.644
ROSS. HONEY. IT'S A NICE COUCH.

118
00:05:00.668 --> 00:05:02.267
IT'S NOT A MAGIC COUCH.

119
00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:05.437
YOU PICKED A GREAT COUCH.

120
00:05:05.506 --> 00:05:06.705
YEAH?

121
00:05:06.774 --> 00:05:08.518
YEAH. COULD YOU JUST
SIGN RIGHT HERE. PLEASE?

122
00:05:08.542 --> 00:05:10.186
OH. SURE. WHOA. WHOA. WHAT'S...?

123
00:05:10.210 --> 00:05:13.612
THE DELIVERY CHARGE IS
ALMOST AS MUCH AS THE COUCH.

124
00:05:13.681 --> 00:05:15.046
WAIT. NO. THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

125
00:05:15.115 --> 00:05:16.926
COME ON. HE LIVES
THREE BLOCKS AWAY.

126
00:05:16.950 --> 00:05:18.227
YEAH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

127
00:05:18.251 --> 00:05:19.896
I'LL TAKE IT MYSELF. THANK YOU.

128
00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:21.765
ALL RIGHT. RACH.
COME ON. LET'S GO.

129
00:05:21.789 --> 00:05:23.588
YEAH.

130
00:05:28.895 --> 00:05:31.363
ARE YOU KIDDING?

131
00:05:31.432 --> 00:05:33.176
NO. COME ON. IT'S
ONLY THREE BLOCKS.

132
00:05:33.200 --> 00:05:34.533
IT'S NOT VERY HEAVY.

133
00:05:34.601 --> 00:05:35.701
TRY IT. COME ON.

134
00:05:40.307 --> 00:05:41.873
OH! OH. I<i> CAN</i> DO IT.

135
00:05:41.942 --> 00:05:43.208
YEAH.

136
00:05:43.276 --> 00:05:44.854
YOU TWO WILL REALLY
ENJOY THAT COUCH.

137
00:05:44.878 --> 00:05:46.345
OH. YEAH. WE'RE. UH...

138
00:05:46.413 --> 00:05:48.146
YEAH. WE'RE NOT TOGETHER.

139
00:05:48.215 --> 00:05:49.881
OH. OKAY.

140
00:05:51.151 --> 00:05:53.111
SOMETHING DIDN'T
QUITE ADD UP THERE.

141
00:05:58.291 --> 00:05:59.624
ROSS...

142
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:00.892
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

143
00:06:00.961 --> 00:06:02.394
ROSS...

144
00:06:02.463 --> 00:06:05.196
WELL. YOU... HER...

145
00:06:05.265 --> 00:06:06.998
I MEAN. SHE'S VERY...

146
00:06:07.067 --> 00:06:08.633
YOU KNOW...

147
00:06:08.702 --> 00:06:10.402
AND YOU'RE. LIKE...

148
00:06:10.471 --> 00:06:12.337
YOU KNOW...

149
00:06:14.541 --> 00:06:18.643
NOT THAT IT'S ANY OF YOUR
BUSINESS. BUT WE<i> DID</i> GO OUT.

150
00:06:18.712 --> 00:06:19.956
REALLY? YOU TWO?

151
00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:21.312
YEAH. RACH?

152
00:06:21.382 --> 00:06:23.526
I REALLY DON'T WANT TO
BE DOING THIS RIGHT NOW.

153
00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:25.016
I'M CARRYING A VERY HEAVY COUCH.

154
00:06:25.085 --> 00:06:27.552
THEN TELL HIM QUICKLY.

155
00:06:27.621 --> 00:06:29.988
FINE. WE WENT OUT.

156
00:06:30.056 --> 00:06:32.457
NOT ONLY DID WE GO OUT.

157
00:06:32.526 --> 00:06:35.560
WE DID IT... 298 TIMES.

158
00:06:35.629 --> 00:06:37.562
ROSS!

159
00:06:37.631 --> 00:06:39.564
OH. MY...

160
00:06:39.633 --> 00:06:41.566
OH! YOU KEPT COUNT?!

161
00:06:41.635 --> 00:06:43.568
YOU ARE SUCH A LOSER.

162
00:06:43.637 --> 00:06:48.607
A LOSER YOU DID
IT WITH 298 TIMES!

163
00:06:53.113 --> 00:06:54.312
OH! OH!

164
00:06:54.381 --> 00:06:55.625
MA'AM! EXCUSE ME. MA'AM?

165
00:06:55.649 --> 00:06:56.748
YES?

166
00:06:56.817 --> 00:06:59.350
YOU CAN'T PUT YOUR
CIGARETTE OUT ON A TREE.

167
00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:01.219
YEAH. I CAN. IT
WORKED REAL WELL.

168
00:07:01.288 --> 00:07:03.021
NO. BUT YOU SHOULDN'T.

169
00:07:03.089 --> 00:07:05.301
SO DON'T EVER DO THAT AGAIN.

170
00:07:05.325 --> 00:07:06.491
I WON'T...

171
00:07:06.560 --> 00:07:08.660
TILL I HAVE MY NEXT CIGARETTE.

172
00:07:08.729 --> 00:07:09.994
HOLD IT.

173
00:07:10.063 --> 00:07:12.041
N.Y.P.D. FREEZE. PUNK.

174
00:07:12.065 --> 00:07:13.598
WHAT?

175
00:07:13.667 --> 00:07:15.033
YEAH. THAT'S RIGHT.

176
00:07:15.101 --> 00:07:16.601
YOU ARE SO BUSTED.

177
00:07:17.671 --> 00:07:18.837
UH. BOOK 'EM.

178
00:07:20.507 --> 00:07:21.840
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

179
00:07:21.909 --> 00:07:23.842
SAVE IT. RED!

180
00:07:23.911 --> 00:07:26.423
UNLESS YOU WANT TO SPEND
THE NIGHT IN THE SLAMMER

181
00:07:26.447 --> 00:07:27.891
YOU'LL APOLOGIZE TO THE TREE.

182
00:07:27.915 --> 00:07:30.882
I AM NOT GOING TO
APOLOGIZE TO A TREE.

183
00:07:30.951 --> 00:07:33.229
YOU APOLOGIZE TO
THE TREE RIGHT NOW

184
00:07:33.253 --> 00:07:35.653
OR I AM CALLING FOR BACKUP.

185
00:07:37.390 --> 00:07:38.757
BACKUP! BACKUP!

186
00:07:38.826 --> 00:07:40.659
I-I'M SORRY! SORRY!

187
00:07:40.727 --> 00:07:41.805
OKAY. CANCEL BACKUP!

188
00:07:41.829 --> 00:07:43.995
CANCEL BACKUP!

189
00:07:45.666 --> 00:07:46.932
OKAY.

190
00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:48.280
ROSS. DIDN'T YOU SAY

191
00:07:48.335 --> 00:07:50.079
THAT THERE WAS AN
ELEVATOR IN HERE?

192
00:07:50.103 --> 00:07:52.671
UH. YES. I DID. BUT
THERE ISN'T. OKAY.

193
00:07:52.739 --> 00:07:54.973
WELL. THEN. WAIT. DON'T
YOU THINK WE SHOULD

194
00:07:55.041 --> 00:07:57.442
MAYBE RETHINK THE WHOLE
HIRING MOVERS THING?

195
00:07:57.511 --> 00:07:58.977
NO WAY! THEY'RE A RIP-OFF.

196
00:07:59.045 --> 00:08:00.278
AND YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE?

197
00:08:00.347 --> 00:08:01.847
THEY CHECK OUT YOUR STUFF

198
00:08:01.915 --> 00:08:03.793
AND COME BACK
LATER AND STEAL IT.

199
00:08:03.817 --> 00:08:05.650
IT'S TRUE. I SAW IT ON<i> DATELINE.</i>

200
00:08:05.719 --> 00:08:07.151
OH. I LOVE<i> DATELINE.</i>

201
00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:09.654
JANE PAULEY IS THE
ONE WOMAN I WOULD KISS.

202
00:08:09.723 --> 00:08:11.022
I DON'T KNOW.

203
00:08:11.091 --> 00:08:12.569
THERE'S JUST
SOMETHING ABOUT HER.

204
00:08:12.593 --> 00:08:14.759
RACH. CAN WE CONCENTRATE.

205
00:08:14.828 --> 00:08:16.761
YEAH. FINE.

206
00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:19.263
I LISTENED TO<i> YOUR</i> DUMB STORY.

207
00:08:19.332 --> 00:08:21.265
OKAY. GO LEFT. LEFT.

208
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:22.612
OKAY.

209
00:08:22.636 --> 00:08:23.869
LEFT!

210
00:08:23.937 --> 00:08:25.269
OKAY. YOU KNOW WHAT?

211
00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:27.183
THERE'S NO MORE LEFT LEFT.

212
00:08:27.207 --> 00:08:28.439
OH. OKAY.

213
00:08:28.509 --> 00:08:30.353
YOU KNOW. LIFT IT STRAIGHT
UP OVER YOUR HEAD.

214
00:08:30.377 --> 00:08:31.543
STRAIGHT UP OVER YOUR HEAD.

215
00:08:31.612 --> 00:08:32.544
YOU CAN DO IT.

216
00:08:32.613 --> 00:08:33.613
YOU CAN DO IT.

217
00:08:34.581 --> 00:08:35.680
OKAY. YOU GOT IT?

218
00:08:35.749 --> 00:08:37.215
YEAH. GO. GO.

219
00:08:37.283 --> 00:08:39.183
OKAY. YOU GOT IT.
RIGHT? YOU GOT IT. RIGHT?

220
00:08:39.252 --> 00:08:40.252
RIGHT. YEAH.

221
00:08:45.559 --> 00:08:48.092
ANY CHANCE YOU THINK THE
COUCH LOOKS GOOD THERE?

222
00:08:50.130 --> 00:08:51.563
SO THIS GUY WAS ALL...

223
00:08:52.766 --> 00:08:54.933
AND I'M ALL.
"BUFFAY... HOMICIDE."

224
00:08:56.503 --> 00:08:58.403
IT WAS JUST SO COOL.

225
00:08:58.471 --> 00:09:00.850
PHOEBE. YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO TAKE THAT BACK.

226
00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:03.742
I KNOW. BUT I'M HAVING SO
MUCH FUN DOING GOOD DEEDS.

227
00:09:03.810 --> 00:09:06.377
OKAY. BUT IMPERSONATING A
POLICE OFFICER'S A SERIOUS THING.

228
00:09:06.446 --> 00:09:07.579
YOU COULD GET ARRESTED.

229
00:09:07.648 --> 00:09:10.281
<i>YOU</i> COULD GET
ARRESTED RIGHT NOW!

230
00:09:12.853 --> 00:09:14.831
ALL RIGHT. YEAH. I
BETTER TAKE IT BACK.

231
00:09:14.855 --> 00:09:16.788
I'M TOTALLY DRUNK WITH POWER.

232
00:09:19.826 --> 00:09:20.759
HEY.

233
00:09:20.827 --> 00:09:22.193
HEY.

234
00:09:22.262 --> 00:09:23.762
OH. I...

235
00:09:25.899 --> 00:09:26.899
HI. JOE.

236
00:09:26.934 --> 00:09:28.044
YEAH... I DIDN'T KNOW YOU GUYS

237
00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:29.145
WERE GOING TO BE HERE.

238
00:09:29.169 --> 00:09:30.301
HEY. JOEY?

239
00:09:30.370 --> 00:09:32.470
DO ME A FAVOR.
SWEETIE. TASTE THIS.

240
00:09:32.539 --> 00:09:33.819
WHAT? WHY?

241
00:09:33.874 --> 00:09:34.973
IT'S OKAY. JOE.

242
00:09:35.042 --> 00:09:36.675
SHE'S A TRAINED CHEF.

243
00:09:36.743 --> 00:09:40.344
UH... ACTUALLY. I WAS
LOOKING FOR PHOEBE.

244
00:09:41.982 --> 00:09:43.882
YOU JUST MISSED HER.

245
00:09:43.951 --> 00:09:45.750
OH. WAS THAT HER?

246
00:09:45.819 --> 00:09:46.484
UH-HUH.

247
00:09:46.553 --> 00:09:47.852
OH. I GOT TO GO.

248
00:09:47.921 --> 00:09:49.187
JOEY. WAIT A MINUTE.

249
00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:50.521
WHAT IS GOING ON WITH YOU?

250
00:09:50.591 --> 00:09:51.790
NOTHING.

251
00:09:51.858 --> 00:09:53.670
OH. COME ON. YOU'VE BEEN
